== Further Reading == {{No footnotes|date=June 2018}} * *History of Wakayama City* (Wakayama City History Compilation Office) == See Also == * [[:en:Air raids on Japan|Air raids on Japan]] - Other locations in Wakayama Prefecture, such as {{ill|Shingū|ja|新宮空襲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shingū|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Kainan|ja|海南空襲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kainan|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and {{ill|Tanabe|ja|田辺空襲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanabe|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, were also bombed. ''' [[:en:Bombing of Gifu in World War II|Gifu Air Raid]] - Conducted almost simultaneously with the Wakayama Air Raid. ''' [[:en:Bombing of Sendai in World War II|Sendai Air Raid]] - Also occurred around the same time. ''' {{ill|Sakai Air Raid|ja|堺大空襲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakai Air Raid|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大阪大空襲}} - Followed the Wakayama Air Raid in the early hours of July 10. * {{ill|War Victims Memorial Tower|ja|太平洋戦全国戦災都市空爆死没者慰霊塔|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/War Victims Memorial Tower|qq=}}
