{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11417327]] Wikidata name: Bombing of Wakayama [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:20, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Pathnav|World War II|Pacific War|Battle of Mainland Japan|Air raids on Japan|frame=1}} '''Wakayama Air Raid''' (和歌山大空襲, Wakayama Daikūshū) refers to a series of [[:en:Wakayama (city)|air raids on Wakayama]] conducted by the [[:en:United States Army Air Forces|United States Army Air Forces]] during [[:en:Pacific War|Pacific War]]. The term often specifically refers to the large-scale [[:en:Strategic bombing|strategic bombing]] that targeted the city center of [[:en:Wakayama Prefecture|Wakayama Prefecture]] and [[:en:Wakayama (city)|Wakayama City]] from the late night of [[July 9, 1945]], to the early hours of [[:en:July 10|July 10]].
== Chronology of the Raids == === Air Raids Before July 9, 1945 === The first air raid on Wakayama Prefecture occurred in April 1942, targeting areas such as [[:en:Iwade, Wakayama|Iwade Town]] (now Iwade City) and [[:en:Kokawa, Wakayama|Kokawa Town]] (now Kinokawa City).
